# Architecture: {{ display_name }}

## Overview

{{ display_name }} is a **monorepo** containing two independently deployable applications that communicate over HTTP:

- **`apps/api`** - Symfony {{ php_version }} REST API{% if api_style == "api-platform" %} powered by API Platform{% endif %}
- **`apps/web`** - Next.js (Node {{ node_version }}) frontend using the App Router

A third package, **`packages/shared-types`**, holds TypeScript interfaces generated from the API schema. It is the single source of truth for the data contract between the two apps.

---

## Monorepo Structure

```
{{ project_name }}/
├── apps/
│   ├── api/              # Symfony backend (PHP {{ php_version }})
│   └── web/              # Next.js frontend (Node {{ node_version }})
├── packages/
│   └── shared-types/     # Auto-generated TypeScript interfaces
├── docs/                 # Architecture, ADRs, page templates
{% if use_docker %}
├── docker/               # Dockerfiles and nginx config
{% endif %}
└── scripts/              # Developer helper scripts
```

**Why a monorepo?**
Atomic commits that span both the API change and the consuming frontend code prevent the repo from getting into a state where the two sides disagree. Shared types catch breaking changes at compile time rather than at runtime.

---

## Communication: API-First

The frontend **never accesses the database directly**. All data flows through the HTTP API.

```
┌──────────────┐     HTTPS/JSON     ┌──────────────────┐
│  Next.js     │  ─────────────►   │  Symfony API     │
│  (apps/web)  │  ◄─────────────   │  (apps/api)      │
└──────────────┘                   └──────────┬───────┘
                                              │ Doctrine ORM
                                   ┌──────────▼───────┐
                                   │  {{ database | capitalize }}  DB  │
                                   └──────────────────┘
```

{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
API Platform generates an OpenAPI 3.1 spec at `/api/docs.json`. The `packages/shared-types` package runs `openapi-typescript` against this spec to produce TypeScript types. Run `pnpm --filter shared-types generate` after changing any API resource.
{% else %}
Shared types in `packages/shared-types/src/index.ts` are maintained by hand. When you change a response shape in Symfony, update the corresponding interface in that package before updating the frontend service layer.
{% endif %}

