## Frontend Architecture (apps/web)

The frontend uses the **Next.js App Router**. The rendering strategy is chosen per page:

- **Server Components** for initial data fetching (no client-side loading spinners for the first paint)
- **Client Components** (`"use client"`) for interactive elements (forms, modals, real-time updates)

### Directory Structure

```
src/
├── app/                  # App Router - every folder is a route segment
│   ├── layout.tsx        # Root layout (providers, global nav)
│   ├── page.tsx          # Home / redirect
│   ├── (auth)/           # Auth route group (login, register)
│   └── (dashboard)/      # Dashboard route group (protected pages)
├── components/
│   ├── ui/               # Primitive components{% if ui_library == "shadcn-ui" %} (shadcn/ui wrappers){% elif ui_library == "radix-ui" %} (Radix UI wrappers){% endif %}
│   └── features/         # Feature-specific composed components
├── hooks/                # Custom React hooks (useAuth, usePagination, etc.)
├── lib/
│   ├── api.ts            # Configured fetch wrapper with auth headers
│   └── utils.ts          # General utilities (cn, formatDate, etc.)
├── services/             # One file per API resource (users.ts, products.ts)
├── types/                # Local types not shared with the backend
└── public/               # Static assets
```

### Data Fetching Pattern

```
Page (Server Component)
  └── calls service function (services/users.ts)
        └── calls lib/api.ts (fetch with Authorization header)
              └── receives JSON from Symfony
                    └── typed via packages/shared-types
```

Server Components fetch data during SSR. The rendered HTML arrives at the browser with data already present. Client Components are used only when the user needs to interact with the data (e.g. edit a form, trigger a mutation).

### Styling

{% if styling == "tailwind" %}
**Tailwind CSS** is the primary styling tool. Utility classes are composed in component files. The `cn()` helper (from `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`) resolves class conflicts cleanly.
{% elif styling == "css-modules" %}
**CSS Modules** scope styles to individual components. Each component has a `.module.css` sibling file. Global styles and design tokens live in `src/app/globals.css`.
{% elif styling == "scss" %}
**SCSS** with CSS Modules scopes styles to components. Design tokens (colors, spacing, typography) are defined in `src/styles/_variables.scss` and imported where needed.
{% endif %}

{% if ui_library == "shadcn-ui" %}
**shadcn/ui** provides copy-paste accessible components built on Radix UI primitives. Components live in `src/components/ui/` and are owned by this project (not installed as an opaque package).
{% elif ui_library == "radix-ui" %}
**Radix UI** primitives provide accessible, unstyled base components. Custom styles are applied on top via the project's styling approach.
{% endif %}

Design direction: **{{ design_style }}**
{% if design_style == "minimal-clean" %}
- Generous whitespace, restrained color palette (neutrals + one accent)
- Strong typographic hierarchy
- Subtle borders and shadows - no decorative chrome
{% elif design_style == "corporate-professional" %}
