## Shared Types (packages/shared-types)

```
packages/shared-types/
├── src/
│   └── index.ts          # All exported TypeScript interfaces
├── package.json
└── tsconfig.json
```

{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
Types are generated from the OpenAPI spec that API Platform exposes at `/api/docs.json`:

```bash
# Regenerate after any Entity or ApiResource change
pnpm --filter shared-types generate
```

The generation script (`packages/shared-types/scripts/generate.ts`) calls `openapi-typescript` and writes the output to `src/index.ts`. Commit the generated file - it is the contract artefact.
{% else %}
Types are maintained by hand. The golden rule: **change the type in `shared-types` first, then update the Symfony serializer output and the frontend service simultaneously in the same commit**. This makes contract drift visible at review time.
{% endif %}

The frontend imports from `@{{ project_name }}/shared-types`:
```typescript
import type { User, PaginatedResponse } from '@{{ project_name }}/shared-types';
```

