{% if use_docker %}
## Docker Architecture

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Docker Compose Network: {{ project_name }}_default              │
│                                                    │
│  nginx (:80/:443) ── reverse proxy                 │
│    ├── /api/*  ──► symfony-fpm (:9000)             │
│    └── /*      ──► nextjs (:3000)                  │
│                                                    │
│  symfony-fpm                                       │
│    └── depends_on: {{ database }}{% if use_rabbitmq %}, rabbitmq{% endif %}{% if use_redis %}, redis{% endif %}                  │
│                                                    │
│  nextjs                                            │
│    └── NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://nginx/api        │
│                                                    │
│  {{ database }}{% if database == "postgresql" %} (:5432){% else %} (:3306){% endif %}                                   │
{% if use_redis %}│  redis (:6379)                                     │
{% endif %}{% if use_rabbitmq %}│  rabbitmq (:5672, management :15672)               │
{% endif %}└────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Each service has its own `Dockerfile`. The `docker/` directory holds:
- `docker/php/Dockerfile` - PHP-FPM image for the Symfony app
- `docker/node/Dockerfile` - Node image for the Next.js app
- `docker/nginx/nginx.conf` - Reverse proxy routing

`docker-compose.yml` is in the repo root. A `docker-compose.override.yml` (gitignored) can hold developer-specific overrides.
{% endif %}

